column5: Good morning of trout fishing Beautifull weather but wind was brutal at 30 km+.Plus zipper broke on my jacket so bit of a cool ride.put bottom of jacket inside my bibs so at least it wasn't flopping in the wind .But worth it.lol.Trout were pretty big today so I kept a 22"+ fish and let rest go as they were all over 22".was only going to keep one anyways.+6on my way home.Had plenty of action but a few wouldnt bute just chase lure to the top then i let line out and they chase it to the bottom.crazy fish.Snow defiantly getting wet.
how much ice do you think??
My auger is 36" and I kicked snow away to hard pack and had around 5"" left to the motor so roughly 31" of ice with about 6"of white frozen slush.
Good idea I'll keep it quite!!only you and I know cheeks!!

No matter what ice will be gone before the 3 rd week of May.Historically it's gone around May 6-8.today already surface snow was melting with +6c.Main thing is getting our nighttime Temps to stay at 0c or above.Its amazing how fast it can go.
ya never know,North America weather is something else these days.Let's hope for the best!
